<http://scilake-project.eu/res/bbf33015#offset_5792_7109>
        a                         nif:OffsetBasedString , <dfki:ScientificDocumentPart> ;
        nif:anchorOf              "In this section, we will first outline relevant literature on the IoMusT field. Afterwards, we will present literature related to the three lenses: green and sustainable IoT (lens 1), Sustainable HCI (lens 2), and Sustainable Development Goals defined by the United Nation (lens 3). The IoMusT presents a series of critical aspects in terms of system's performance that are particularly interesting to study when facing the topic of sustainability: indeed, IoMusT applications include a wide variety of requirements, ranging from low-speed information processing to streaming and processing of high-bandwidth data streams with stringent real-time requirements. Additionally, IoMusT is driven by artists, a type of professional that bases their practices on projects that are usually visionary and open to exploring the new possibilities that cutting-edge technologies offer. This makes the IoMusT a very populated source of case studies that fit with the relatively new topic of sustainability within the field of the IoT. To summarize, the IoMusT functions as a getaway that, in line with the holistic approach presented, allows our research to touch topics that are very specific and, therefore, challenging from a performance point of view, as well as topics that are more broadly applicable to the IoT in general." ;
        nif:beginIndex            "5792"^^xsd:nonNegativeInteger ;
        nif:endIndex              "7109"^^xsd:nonNegativeInteger ;
        nif:referenceContext      <http://scilake-project.eu/res/bbf33015> ;
